  The foreign trade balance during 11 months of 1993 was 
positive in the amount of $13.8 billion (for the corresponding 
period of last year it was positive in the amount of $4.1 
billion). 
  The balance of payments of Russia (not including 
the CIS countries) during January-November 1993 was 
characterized by a positive foreign trade balance and growth of 
foreign assets of commercial banks and state reserves of Russia: 


