<H3> <TI>   Foreign Ministry Body Discusses East Europe Policy </TI></H3>
<H4>   Foreign Policy Council Meets </H4>
<F P=102> 944Q0170A Moscow DIPLOMATICHESKIY VESTNIK in Russian No 
23-24, Dec 93 [Signed to press 22 Dec 93] pp 58-59--FOR OFFICIAL </F>



<TEXT>
USE ONLY 
<F P=103> 944Q0170A </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow DIPLOMATICHESKIY VESTNIK </F>
 Language: <F P=105>Russian </F>
Article Type:CSO 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report under the rubric: "Diplomacy, Science, </F>
Public: Meeting of the Foreign Policy Council under the Russian 
Federation Ministry of Foreign Affairs: The New Situation in 
East Europe and Russia's Foreign Policy"] 
  [Text] 
  This pro blem was the topic of discussion at the scheduled 
meeting of the Foreign Policy Council under the Russian 
Federation MFA [Ministry of Foreign Affairs], which took place 
on 3 November. Minister of Foreign Affairs A.V. Kozyrev chaired 
the meeting, which was conducted by the Deputy Minister of 
Foreign Affairs S.B. Krylov. 
  Among the participants in the council's work were noted 
scholars on international affairs, political scientists, 
representatives from business circles and the Russian Orthodox 
Church, journalists, and diplomats. The meeting participants 
analyzed from a conceptual and practical angle the fundamental 
approaches in Russia's foreign policy toward countries of the 
East European region. 
  The tone of the meeting was set by A.V. Kozyrev's speech, 
which we publish below. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-42871 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "jpusr001__l94008" </HT>


<HEADER>
