<ABS>  FBIS Report: Central Eurasia </ABS>
<DATE1>   24 February 1994 </DATE1>
<F P=100> RUSSIA </F>
<F P=101> POLITICAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   News of Political Parties, Leaders </TI></H3>
<H4>   Democratic Union To Organize `White Guard' </H4>
<F P=102> 944F0292A Moscow MOSKOVSKIY KOMSOMOLETS in Russian 25 Jan 94 
p 1 </F>

<F P=103> 944F0292A </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow MOSKOVSKIY KOMSOMOLETS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:CSO 

<F P=106> [Article by Aleksandr Mitrofanov: "White Terror Announced: </F>
Novodvorskaya Tries on Kornilov Tunic"] 
  [Text] A truly historical party meeting of capital 
organizations of the Russian Democratic Union was held in Moscow 
during the last days off. 
  "We decided to deal with the Communists with our own forces, 
and to switch to white terror." Valeriya Novodvorskaya, leader 
of the DS [Democratic Union], agreed to comment for MOSKOVSKIY 
KOMSOMOLETS on the results of the party gathering of radicals. 
"To personally see to it that the newspaper ZAVTRA does not come 
out, that they do not conduct their rallies, and that communist 
and fascist symbols do not appear on the streets. To establish 
in Moscow detachments of White Guards, which already exist in 
the country--Kornilov detachments with very nice skulls on their 
sleeves. The Constitution and the president have no support 
other than self-defense and even attacks of the anti-Communists. 
Because it is stupid to defend ourselves from them with words." 
  Well, then, does Valeriya intend to physically destroy the 
Reds? "Well, to start with, physically as well," says Miss 
Novodvorskaya. "We simply want them just to sit at home and be 
afraid to come out on the street." 
  There are about 50 people now in the Moscow Democratic 
Union, 
but what kind! All those who had a "propensity for socialism or 
cowardice" were discharged from the Democratic Union back in 
March, according to Novodvorskaya. And now the Democratic Union 
"represents a potential combat organization, only not a social 
revolutionary one, but one that is completely White Guard." 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-42889 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "jpusr017___94015" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-USR-94-017 </AU>
Document Type:JPRS 
Document Title: 

</HEADER>

<ABS>  FBIS Report: Central Eurasia </ABS>
<DATE1>   24 February 1994 </DATE1>
<F P=100> RUSSIA </F>
<F P=101> POLITICAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   News of Political Parties, Leaders </TI></H3>
<H4>   Pamyat Denied Official Registration </H4>
<F P=102> 944F0292B Moscow KURANTY in Russian 25 Jan 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> 944F0292B </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow KURANTY </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:CSO 

<F P=106> [Article by Viktor Mironov: "V.V.Zh Has Disagreements with </F>
Pamyat"] 
  [Text] Mr. Zhirinovskiy is a programmed computer 
filled with the positions and postures of all the parties," 
believes Dmitriy Vasilyev, leader of the national patriotic 
front Pamyat. 
  He spoke yesterday at a press conference on the occasion of 
the refusal of the Ministry of Justice of Russia to register his 
front's charter. Assessing this kind of reaction by the state 
organ as "genocide against Russian thought and the Russian right 
to a world outlook and a political position," Vasilyev continued 
his tirade directed at V.V.Zh. He called absolutely groundless 
the suppositions that Pamyat and the LDPR [Liberal Democratic 
Party of Russia] are united. In his opinion, this Liberal 
Democrat preaches ideas of national socialism, and his 
militaristic statements set the Russian people against other 
people and states. The statement that the Russian boot will be 
washed by the waters of the Indian Ocean is political 
adventurism, if not political provocation. 
  The Pamyat leader said that V.V.Zh. "likes to call himself a 
Russian and speak in behalf of the Russian people. But it is 
necessary to be honest and not hide his nationality." 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

